news.title: Complexes in HBR Layout razed, Bengaluru development body reclaims Rs 100 crore properties
news.para: Equipped with bulldozers and accompanied by over 200 policemen, the team arrived at HBR Layout, northeast Bengaluru, and began clearing buildings that had come up on BDA-acquired plots.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal colony crackdown top focus for new town planner
news.para: But after taking charge on Tuesday, Amit Madholia said that preventing development of illegal colonies and stopping unauthorised construction would be his top priorities.

news.title: Nagpur: 15 days on, EoW yet to act on NIT land scam complaint
news.para: As reported by TOI, the NIT had lodged complaints with the EoW on June 13 claiming that five people in nexus with officials of the city survey office-II got got mutation done on its two parcels of land worth around Rs 74 crore.

news.title: Seven buildings sealed, notices sent to 599: Ahmedabad fire department to Gujarat HC
news.para: In an affidavit, the fire department stated that since the HC order passed on June 14, out of the 26 commercial highrise buildings without fire NOCs, two obtained fire NOCs and nine others applied for renewal of their NOCs.

news.title: Noida: Farmhouse owners list 'rules' to oppose demolition drive
news.para: Hearing a bunch of petitions by farmhouse owners from Sector 135, the high court had directed the authority to maintain status quo for the next 20 days.

news.title: Building crashes have killed over 800 people in Mumbai in 50 years
news.para: According to information received from Mhada under RTI by activist Jeetendra Ghadge, between 1970 and 2018, 815 people have lost their lives in building crashes.

news.title: Haryana: Properties to get unique IDs in urban areas soon
news.para: The term ‘Lal Dora’, which literally translates to red thread, was coined during the British regime and refers to the practice of drawing red lines on maps to demarcate agricultural areas from non-agricultural plots.

news.title: Mumbai: Sai Builders' Deepak Lohana arrested for cheating doctor of Rs 4 crore
news.para: Lohana was produced before the 37th Metropolitan Magistrate's court which remanded him in police custody till July 3. The complainant, Kailash Kothari, said a property agent had introduced him to Sai Builders' partners.

news.title: ED traces Rs 2,317 crore as 'proceeds of crime' in Yes Bank-DHFL fraud
news.para: The agency suspects that the entire amount received by Yes Bank to DHFL has been laundered by the accused brothers Kapil and Dheeraj Wadhawan. Along with the Wadhawan brother, the promoter of Yes Bank, Rana Kapoor has been arrested in the said case.

news.title: India Cements completes acquisition of SMPL
news.para: "The entire equity and preference shares of SMPL are acquired at a total consideration of Rs 182.89 crore," the company said.

news.title: China Evergrande says winding-up lawsuit won't impact restructuring
news.para: Evergrande confirmed the filing by investment holding firm Top Shine Global Ltd in Hong Kong for not fulfilling a financial obligation of HK$862.5 million ($109.91 million).

news.title: Awfis lease out 65,000 sq ft space to UNext in Bengaluru
news.para: In February 2022, the company had leased 85,000 sq ft space with 1,500 seats in River Side Tower, sector 125, Noida.

news.title: Nagpur survey office mutates land with 800 plots, houses in name of five
news.para: NIT counsel Girish Kunte, following the directives of trust chairman, had fought a four-year-long battle and got the properties registered in NIT’s name again.

news.title: IT Park housing scheme in Chandigarh secures wildlife clearance
news.para: The decision was taken in a meeting of the state wildlife board held under the chairmanship of UT administrator Banwarilal Purohit on Monday.

news.title: Carlyle acquires significant minority stake in Ahmedabad-based Varmora Granito
news.para: Equity for this transaction will come from funds managed and advised by entities affiliated with Carlyle Asia Partners Growth, the US private equity firm said in a statement.
